## Registration Protocol

When Builder Agent creates a new tool, Zeus adds a row using this template:

```
| {name} | {skill/hook/command/subagent} | {.cursor/tools/filename.md} | {agent} | {one-sentence purpose} | draft |
```

Status progresses: `draft` → `active` after Zeus verifies it works on a real task → `deprecated` when superseded.

### Promotion criteria (draft → active)

A draft skill or tool is promoted to `active` when **all** of these are met:

1. **Used on a real task** — the tool was invoked during actual work (not just created)
2. **Output verified** — Zeus confirmed the output matched the declared contract
3. **No rework needed** — the tool did not require immediate fixes after first use
4. **Content is complete** — the file has real instructions, not placeholder text

Draft items that have not been promoted within **30 days** of creation should be reviewed: either complete them or remove them from the registry.

