## Tool Types Explained

### Skill
A reusable capability that an agent can invoke repeatedly.
Example: `validate-spring-dto` — checks a DTO for `@Valid` annotations and constraint coverage.

### Hook
Triggered automatically by an event (file save, task close, git commit).
Example: `task-close` — on session `stop`, appends a session marker to `tasks/todo.md`.

### Command
Explicitly invoked by Zeus or the user with a specific trigger phrase.
Example: [`cmd-security-scan`](.cursor/commands/cmd-security-scan.md) — `/cmd-security-scan`, OWASP-style review on current diff or scoped paths.

### Subagent
A fully defined agent spun up for a focused, bounded task then retired.
Example: `db-migration-agent` — handles a single schema migration, then decommissioned.

